# n8n Rules

- One workflow = one responsibility (one business process)
- Avoid large multi-purpose workflows; split and chain via HTTP/queue
- **Business logic lives in Backend** — n8n only schedules and coordinates
- Enable retries on HTTP/nodes that call backend
- Configure Error Workflow for failure notification
- Prefer queue-backed triggers for Apply Worker and similar jobs
- Pass stable IDs and correlation IDs in payloads for observability
- Do not embed LLM prompts or scraping steps inside n8n
